{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/210/comments/37543774.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim/issues/210#comment-37543774"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim/issues/210.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 210, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/srcsim.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/srcsim"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}ts=c_plus_plus"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "srcsim", "full_name": "osrf/srcsim", "uuid": "{c41021d9-0217-4628-999d-7f8d82f98dcb}"}, "title": "Harness after advancing checkpoint can fail to exit state 4"}, "content": {"raw": "I've seen this also. Sometimes, you can just detach and it will stand successfully:\n\n~~~\nrostopic pub -1 /valkyrie/harness/detach std_msgs/Bool true\n~~~\n\nIf you're going to reharness anyway, you might was well try detaching first to see if it stands.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I've seen this also. Sometimes, you can just detach and it will stand successfully:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span>rostopic pub -1 /valkyrie/harness/detach std_msgs/Bool true\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>If you're going to reharness anyway, you might was well try detaching first to see if it stands.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2017-06-13T04:37:15.606083+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Steve Peters", "uuid": "{2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1fb4816dad9e68337d3096f750951f6cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSP-1.png"}}, "nickname": "Steven Peters", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:5de38267-b118-494c-aa76-4fab35448816"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comm